newsitem.title: UK: NWE jet slips with gas oil futures, prems holding.
newsitem.headline: NWE jet slips with gas oil futures, prems holding.

text.p: European jet fuel premiums were steady on Thursday, but outright prices were up $2-3 a tonne weaker on the back of easier IPE futures.
March IPE gas oil closed $2.50 lower at $173.50.
Traders said activity was still thin, but a 1,000 tonne barge traded at March IPE +$24.75 fob Rotterdam in the morning. Delivery will be by the end of February.
Cargo premiums were also broadly steady around +$26 cif NWE.
